                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/864: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marriner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-18T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 18, 1935—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 18—4:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>703. Have just been informed that negotiations over the Abyssinian affair have
                    broken down due to Mussolini’s intransigent attitude as communicated to Laval by
                    Aloisi this morning. The British delegation is preparing to leave tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marriner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
